# Project 2 — E-Commerce Homepage Wireframe
This project was completed as part of the UI/UX Internship assessment at DecodeLabs.
 Objective
Design a low-fidelity desktop wireframe for an e-commerce homepage focused on improving:
- User navigation
- Product discoverability
- Checkout clarity
- Trust-building experience

The wireframe was created with a strong focus on usability, layout hierarchy, and user flow instead of visual styling.
Tools Used
- Figma
- Wireframing Principles
- UX Planning & Layout Structuring

##  Features Included
- Sticky Navigation Bar
- Hero Section with CTA
- Feature / Trust Strip
- Product Grid Layout
- Checkout Flow Visualization
- Trust & Security Section
- Structured Footer Navigation

## UX Focus Areas
- Clear navigation hierarchy
- Reduced checkout friction
- Better product visibility
- Improved interaction flow
- Simple and intuitive layout planning

##  Learning Outcome
Through this project, I explored:
- Low-fidelity wireframing
- Layout planning
- UX-focused structuring
- E-commerce interaction flow
- Visual hierarchy fundamentals

